    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>You hold the ring fragment in one hand, though it seems like this should be impossible. The small thing is incredibly heavy. 

A small protrusion extrudes from one end of this fragment.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>This ring fragment is marked by the protrusion coming out of one end.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine Areph.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine Areph again. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>Put the ring fragments away.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>Put the ring away.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>You direct a powerful surge of the Tides at the unseen force holding the ring fragments apart, picturing it in your mind as a physical presence, a hostile if nameless entity.

The moment the force is pushed back, the fragments lurch towards each other and the ring willingly reforms before your eyes. It is now obvious why it was not reforged previously, as only a castoff or a nearly superhuman effort could have done so. The complete Shadow Ring lies in the palm of your hand, simmering with barely restrained power.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>Pocket the ring.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
